253.6	Edward_Bernays	Edward Bernays	Edward Louis Bernays (November 22, 1891 â€“ March 9, 1995), was an Austrian-American pioneer in the field of public relations and propaganda, referred to in his obituary as "the father of public relations". He combined the ideas of Gustave Le Bon and Wilfred Trotter on crowd psychology with the psychoanalytical ideas of his uncle, Sigmund Freud.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/c/ca/Edward_Bernays.jpg/220px-Edward_Bernays.jpg
